               <head>Rare collection of Sufi works by ‘Aziz Nasafi, 18 works (a-r)</head>
               <msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807">
                  <summary>Rare collection of Sufi analects prefixed with a separate preface by ʿAbd al-ʿAzīz ibn Muḥammad al-Nasafī (d. circa 661/1262). Volume not dated; datable to the mid sixteenth century. Neat, minute nastaʿlīq with occasional shikastah flourishes. The hand is broadly consistent as the work of a single scribe (unnamed). Stamped foliation. Lacks original binding. Original text cropped, cut and remounted with new margins in gutter. Folios subsequently rebound in IOL red half leather binding, stamp dated 21 Oct 1935. Folios slightly damaged by wormholes, cropped margins, and occasional stains. Labels from the earlier wrapper remounted at beginning. Condition moderately fragile. </summary>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1198-item1">
                     <locus from="1v" to="6v">ff. 1v-6v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item a. 
</p>
                        <p>Rare Sufi treatise prefixed to the present collection of (independent) works intended as a preface to the whole volume, defined here as a majmūʿah or anthology, by ʿAbd al-ʿAzīz ibn Muḥammad al-Nasafī (d. circa 661/1262), prepared at the behest of his friends. 
</p>
                        <p>The work consists of five chapters, each termed faṣl. 
</p>
                        <p>The text extends into margins. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                        <p>The work is prefixed on folio 1r with miscellaneous annotations consisting of a qiṭʿah, an Arabic ḥadīs̲ of the <persName key="viaf_97245226" role="ant">Prophet Muḥammad</persName> with interlinear Persian translation, and a further Arabic note on the building of tombs and the slaughter of unbelievers. 
                        </p>
                     </note>
